description:
As we study the history of the French Revolution, we discover that it was Rome's policy that had wrought the social, political, and religious conditions that were hurrying France on to ruin. This means that it was Popery's agenda that destroyed France's economy, subtly promoted immorality, and atheism. The Papacy, according to the Bible, and from her own mouth, never changes; she is the same Rome as of old. Inspiration reveals that the same teachings and conditions that led to the French Revolution will be repeated and affect the entire world, beginning in America. Study with us and uncover the hidden agenda behind the increase of minimum wage, the promotion of licentious practices, and the prevalence of man-made disasters and calamities. "The policy of Rome had wrought out those conditions, social, political, and religious, that were hurrying France on to ruin." {The Great Controversy, 276.4}   
"At the same time anarchy is seeking to sweep away all law, not only divine, but human. The centralizing of wealth and power; the vast combinations for the enriching of the few at the expense of the many; the combinations of the poorer classes for the defense of their interests and claims; the spirit of unrest, of riot and bloodshed; the world-wide dissemination of the same teachings that led to the French Revolution--all are tending to involve the whole world in a struggle similar to that which convulsed France."  {Education, 228.2}
fulltitle: Increase Minimum Wage, Immorality, Calamities-The Hidden Agenda
